section.title: Freestyle Predicates (freestyle.predicates)
section.paragraph: This module contains predicates operating on vertices (0D elements) and polylines (1D elements). It is also intended to be a collection of examples for predicate definition in Python.
User-defined predicates inherit one of the following base classes, depending on the object type (0D or 1D) to operate on and the arity (unary or binary):

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Interface1D is a contour. An Interface1D is a contour if it is borded by a different shape on each of its sides.

field_body.paragraph: True if the Interface1D is a contour, false otherwise.

list_item.paragraph: threshold (float) – The value of the threshold density. Any Interface1D having a density lower than this threshold will match.
sigma (float) – The sigma value defining the density evaluation window size used in the freestyle.functions.DensityF0D functor.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the density evaluated for the Interface1D is less than a user-defined density value.

field_body.paragraph: True if the density is lower than a threshold.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Interface1D’s time stamp is equal to a certain user-defined value.

field_body.paragraph: True if the time stamp is equal to a user-defined value.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Interface1D’s time stamp is equal to a certain user-defined value.

field_body.paragraph: True if the time stamp is equal to a user-defined value.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Interface1D is an external contour. An Interface1D is an external contour if it is borded by no shape on one of its sides.

field_body.paragraph: True if the Interface1D is an external contour, false otherwise.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the 2D length of inter1 is less than the 2D length of inter2.
Checks whether the two supplied ViewEdges have the same material.

field_body.paragraph: qi (int) – The Quantitative Invisibility you want the Interface1D to have.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Quantitative Invisibility evaluated at an Interface1D, using the freestyle.functions.QuantitativeInvisibilityF1D functor, equals a certain user-defined value.

field_body.paragraph: True if Quantitative Invisibility equals a user-defined value.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if inter1 and inter2 belong to the same shape.
Returns true if the shape to which the Interface1D belongs to has the same freestyle.types.Id as the one specified by the user.

field_body.paragraph: True if Interface1D belongs to the shape of the user-specified Id.

list_item.paragraph: level (int) – The level of the pyramid from which the pixel must be read.
integration_type (freestyle.types.IntegrationType) – The integration method used to compute a single value from a set of values.

sampling (float) – The resolution used to sample the chain: GetViewMapGradientNormF0D is evaluated at each sample point and the result is obtained by combining the resulting values into a single one, following the method specified by integration_type.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the evaluation of the Gradient norm Function is higher for inter1 than for inter2.

list_item.paragraph: xmin (float) – X lower bound of the image boundary.
ymin (float) – Y lower bound of the image boundary.
xmax (float) – X upper bound of the image boundary.
ymax (float) – Y upper bound of the image boundary.

desc_content.paragraph: Returns true if the Interface1D intersects with image boundary.
Check whether an Interface0DIterator references a TVertex and is the one that is hidden (inferred from the context).
